---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import caseStudyImg from "../assets/case-study.png";
import Container from "../design-system/Container.astro";
import Text from "../design-system/Text.astro";
import Button from "../design-system/Button.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section id="case-study" class="relative bg-case-study">
  <Container className="block md:flex">
    <Container inset className="w-1/2 py-20 flex items-center justify-center">
      <Image
        src={caseStudyImg}
        alt="Coming soon illustration"
        class="block w-3/4 mx-auto"
      />
    </Container>
    <Container
      inset
      className="w-1/2 flex items-start justify-center flex-col py-8"
    >
      <Text as="p" size="large" className="mb-4 text-text-light">
        Life-centered design case study
      </Text>
      <h2 class="font-serif font-bold text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-text mb-8">
        Reflections on the Usefulness and Limitations of Tools for Life-centered
        Design
      </h2>
      <Text as="p" size="large" className="text-text-light mb-8">
        Life-centered design is getting a lot of attention. But there is not
        much information available about how to use this approach in practice.
        <br />
        <br />
        To investigate the application of life-centered tools, we did a first person
        study, analyzing a popular flat-pack chair through four tools: systems maps,
        actant maps, product lifecycle maps and behavioural impact canvas.
        <br />
        <br />
        Read how we identified human and non-human actors, understood their interconnectedness,
        and identified gaps in the process.</Text
      >
      <div
        class="flex sm:items-center gap-4 flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch w-full"
      >
        <!-- <Button><Icon name="lucide:arrow-right" />View case study</Button> -->
        <Button
          variant="outlined"
          href="https://dl.designresearchsociety.org/drs-conference-papers/drs2024/researchpapers/198/"
          external><Icon name="lucide:file-text" />View paper</Button
        >
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Container>
</section>
